LanguageData.ARA_EggSpew.label: Lay Egg
LanguageData.ARA_EggSpew.description: Expels a dormant egg from the ovaries. The Arachne Queen can activate it by contact and select the type of overseer to hatch. Check the egg's detailed information for the characteristics of each overseer type.\n\nOnly small swarm units hatch from this egg.
LanguageData.ARA_EggSpew.comps.CompAbilityEffect_Body: Cannot gestate because the ovaries are damaged or missing

LanguageData.ARA_EggSpew_Techprint.label: Gestation Gene Test Egg
LanguageData.ARA_EggSpew_Techprint.description: A special egg expelled from the ovaries that cannot hatch an overseer but can hatch a specific research techprint. The Arachne Queen can activate it by contact.\n\nThis egg operates by consuming a large amount of essence, and which techprint can be hatched depends on the research progress at the time of deployment. Techprints corresponding to ununlocked research cannot be hatched.
LanguageData.ARA_EggSpew_Techprint.comps.CompAbilityE: Requires Research Project Node ESS-5 "Essence Extraction" to unlock skill
LanguageData.ARA_Cocoon_Cloth.label: Fabric Hatching Cocoon
LanguageData.ARA_Cocoon_Cloth.description: Drops a Fabric Cocoon. It contains nutrients and genetic material to hatch a basic set of fabric items. -- Click the cocoon's hyperlink to check the characteristics of all craftable equipment.

LanguageData.ARA_Cocoon_Cloth_From_Death.label: Corpse Weave: Fabric Hatching Cocoon
LanguageData.ARA_Cocoon_Cloth_From_Death.description: Designates a non-rotting or lightly rotted corpse and converts it into a Fabric Cocoon.
